@startuml
actor "Dispatcher" as Dispatcher
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Backend" as Backend
participant "TMS Bridge" as TMSBridge
participant "Azure Service Bus" as ServiceBus

title "Sending Transport Order Information via EDI"

caption
<font color=red>**Focus: Architectural integration (not data contract of DTO)**</font>  
<font color=green>Status: Draft</font>  
Date: 2025-08-14
endcaption


== EDI Communication Flow ==

Dispatcher -> Frontend : Click "Send EDI" button\non customer's list of open items
activate Frontend

Frontend -> Backend : Request to publish\nTransport Order information to EDI
activate Backend

alt #LightYellow Optional: Data Mapping Required
    note right of Backend : To be clarified:\nMapping to target EDI format\n(provided by CAL)
    Backend -> TMSBridge : Request required source data
    activate TMSBridge
    TMSBridge --> Backend : Return source data
    deactivate TMSBridge
    Backend -> Backend : Create EDI DTO from source data
else #LightBlue Alternative: Request Mapped DTO from TMS
    Backend -> TMSBridge : Request mapped DTO
    activate TMSBridge
    TMSBridge --> Backend : Return mapped DTO
    deactivate TMSBridge
end

Backend -> ServiceBus : Send DTO with mapped content
note right of ServiceBus : Details to be defined

alt #LightGreen Success Flow
    ServiceBus --> Backend : Success confirmation
    Backend -> Backend : Mark Transport Order / Tour Info as "sent"
    Backend -> Frontend : Return success message
    deactivate Backend
    Frontend -> Frontend : Display success message
    Frontend --> Dispatcher : Show success notification/message
    note right of Dispatcher : Dispatcher sees\nsuccess notification
    
else #LightSalmon Failure Flow
    ServiceBus --> Backend : Failure to publish
    Backend -> Backend : Mark Transport Order / Tour Info as "failed"
    Backend -> Frontend : Return error message
    deactivate Backend
    Frontend -> Frontend : Display error message
    Frontend --> Dispatcher : Show error and cause
    note right of Dispatcher : Dispatcher is informed\nabout error and cause
end

deactivate Frontend

@enduml